Commentary Text: Tymal Mills to Pant, out Caught by Tim David!! Rash! Rash from the captain and DC are in trouble. Ponting glum! But you can't be too harsh on Pant too. This was short and wide, so the cut was on. But what did him in was Tymal Mills's extra bounce, so it took the outside edge and flew straight to third man. Delhi Capitals have lost three wickets for two runs now and MI winning their first game of an IPL season for the first time since 2012 is looking a bit more realistic! Pant c Tim David b Tymal Mills 1(2)
